review_text: CSA is the only food bank I have found that offers a vegetarian and vegan options. Paul is wonderful. I volunteered under his supervision before the pandemic. name: Community Settlement Association
review_text: Nope Sorry This place does not cater to the needs of people with emotional support service animals. We were asked to leave because someone told us "No Dogs Allowed" and asked where our service animal got her training from. Under penalty of privacy act, after being asked if our dog is a service animal "Your Not Allowed To Ask Any Further Questions" or you can be sued, fired, or held in content for 30 days, for asking questions due to privacy. People like this need to be further trained and certified in Social Services in order to continue to service the homeless. We don't feel welcomed here, until people can respect one another at this facility, we will not be moved for any reason, no amount of apology will be accepted for this kind of behavior. This kind of act makes a business go down, because if one rotten apple can make a bunch look bad, then so can the same for people that work in community places like this. I am completely disgusted with the overall indecent "RUDENESS" and lack of any human kindness to this community facility.

name: Community Settlement Association
review_text:
A community non-profit that offers various social services primarily to folks who live in the Eastside and Downtown. Like others have said, some of the services are low prices for court mandated DUI classes, after school children's program, food bank, community garden, etc.

Aside from all of those amazing services this place has some amazing historical moments. From it's beginning as a farm labor center for Latino to it having been lead by Riverside's Ward 2 Council Member.

name: Community Settlement Association
review_text: I went here as a Court Order because of a DUI I received.  I attended classes and spoke to my Counselor on a weekly basis.  This has been very beneficial to me.  I will have been sober for 3 years on April 14,  2017.
